The paper proposes a novel framework for approximate nearest neighbor search in natural language processing tasks. This problem is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework involves spectral analysis and partitioning of the dataset, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
